<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="38" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1400]" pageId="8" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length: 
<quantity box="[381,508,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="27.5" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="24.0">24–31 mm</quantity>
. This species can be recognized by the angles of the pronotum, which are only slightly extended laterally. The metatibial expansions are broadly dilated for most of their length, ending abruptly near the apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
